# /etc/cron.d/maltytask-document-ingest
#
# Periodic ingest of invoice + delivery-note PDFs from Drive inbox → MySQL.
# Runs scripts/ingest-documents.js from the maltytask pipeline (Node.js).
# Drains the Drive inbox in batches of 50; idempotent (Drive fileId dedup).
#
# Source of truth: db/cron/maltytask-document-ingest.cron in the maltyweb repo.
# Deployed via bin/deploy.sh --apply (sudo install → /etc/cron.d/).
#
# NOTE: CRON IS DISABLED PENDING MANUAL SMOKE TEST.
# Steps to enable after smoke test passes:
#   1. ssh maltyweb
#   2. Uncomment the active line below (remove the leading #)
#   3. sudo cp /var/www/maltytask/db/cron/maltytask-document-ingest.cron \
#             /etc/cron.d/maltytask-document-ingest
#   OR redeploy via bin/deploy.sh --apply (which installs all cron/*.cron).
#
# Pre-flight checklist before enabling:
#   - Smoke test passed: node scripts/ingest-documents.js --dry-run --limit 1
#   - MySQL connection verified: SELECT 1 from pipeline succeeds
#   - secrets/ symlink confirmed: /opt/maltytask-pipeline/secrets/service-account.json
#   - /var/log/maltytask/ingest-documents.log writable by maltytask user
#   - Claude CLI auth: first manual run of a --no-llm pass recommended
#     (claude CLI requires interactive auth on first use; cannot run in cron
#      until operator has authenticated once via `claude` on the VPS)
#
# Timing: every 5 min is appropriate for a manual-upload inbox workflow.
# --limit 50 caps Drive API calls per tick; queue drains across ticks.
# --no-llm prevents runaway LLM calls in unattended mode until LLM fallback
# is validated in production. Remove --no-llm once operator confirms the
# LLM fallback is authenticated and working.
#
# Note: cron syntax for /etc/cron.d/* requires the user column
# (m h dom mon dow user command). Times are UTC (VPS timezone is Etc/UTC).
#
# Manual edits will be overwritten on next deploy. Edit the source file
# in the repo, commit, then run bin/deploy.sh --apply.

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin

# m   h  dom mon dow  user        command

# DISABLED — remove this '#' to activate after smoke test:
# */5  *   *   *   *   maltytask   cd /opt/maltytask-pipeline && HOME=/var/www/maltytask NVM_DIR=/var/www/maltytask/.nvm bash -c '. $NVM_DIR/nvm.sh && node_modules/.bin/tsx scripts/ingest-documents.js --limit 50 --no-llm' >> /var/log/maltytask/ingest-documents.log 2>&1
